==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''additivus''

===Adjective===
#(''[[Math]]'') Proper to be [[add]]ed; [[positive]]; -- opposed to [[subtractive]].

===Noun===
#A [[substance]] added to another substance or [[product]] for its ability to [[improve]] the finished product. Most often in relation to processed food, [[e.g.]], "The pancake mix was perfect until they started mixing in unwholesome '''additives'''" or "Adding ascorbic acid to orange juice increases its shelf life by a factor of two."

